["Alcohol", "September 21, 2018", "Key facts", "(2) The harmful use of alcohol causes 3.3 million deaths each year, representing 5.9% of all deaths.", "The harmful use of alcohol is a factor in more than 200 deaths and injuries.", "(3) Overall, 5.1% of the global burden of disease and injury is attributable to alcohol, as measured by disability-adjusted life years (DALYs).", "Alcohol abuse causes death and disability relatively early in life.", "Almost 25% of all deaths in the 20-39 age group are attributable to alcohol.", "There is a causal relationship between the harmful use of alcohol, a spectrum of mental and behavioral disorders, and other noncommunicable diseases, as well as injuries.", "The latest causal link has been established between harmful use of alcohol and incidence of infectious diseases such as tuberculosis as well as the course of HIV / AIDS.", "Health consequences aside, the harmful use of alcohol results in significant social and economic losses for individuals and society as a whole.", "Alcohol is a psychoactive substance with dependable properties and has been widely used in many cultures over centuries.", "The harmful use of alcohol causes a disease, social and economic burden for societies.", "Alcohol affects people and societies in many ways, depending on the amount of alcohol that is consumed, the pattern of drinking, and, on rare occasions, the quality of the alcohol that is consumed.", "In 2012, about 3.3 million deaths, or 5.9% of all global deaths, were caused by alcohol use.", "Harmful use of alcohol may also harm others, such as family members, friends, co-workers and strangers.", "Moreover, the harmful use of alcohol represents a significant health, social and economic burden on society as a whole.", "Alcohol abuse is a factor in more than 200 illnesses and injuries.", "Drinking alcohol is associated with a risk of health problems such as mental and behavioral disorders, including alcohol dependence, and major noncommunicable diseases such as cirrhosis, some cancers and cardiovascular disease, as well as injuries resulting from violence, road accidents and collisions.", "It is worth noting that a large proportion of the disease burden that can be attributed to harmful drinking arises from intentional and unintentional injuries, including those from traffic accidents, violence and suicides.", "Fatal injuries attributable to alcohol consumption appear to occur in relatively young age groups.", "And the last causal relationship that was discovered was that of the harmful drinking of alcohol, infectious diseases such as tuberculosis, and the pathways of AIDS and HIV infection.", "A pregnant mother's alcohol use may cause fetal alcohol syndrome and preterm labor complications.", "Factors affecting alcohol use and the harm it causes", "At the individual and societal level, a range of factors have been identified that influence the levels and patterns of alcohol consumption and the magnitude of alcohol-related problems in a population.", "Environmental factors include economic development, the dominant culture, availability of alcohol, comprehensiveness and levels of implementation and enforcement of alcohol policies.", "For a certain level or pattern of drinking, weaknesses within a community are likely to lead to distinct effects similar to those found between societies.", "Although there is no single, dominant risk factor, the higher a person\u2019s exposure to risk, the more likely it is that alcohol-related problems will arise as a result of their use.", "The impact of alcohol consumption on the chronic and acute health outcomes of the population is largely determined by two separate, though related, consumption dimensions.", "Total amount of alcohol consumed, and", "Pattern of abuse.", "The context of abuse plays an important role in the occurrence of alcohol-related harm, especially that related to the health impact of alcohol intoxication, and in rare cases the quality of alcohol consumed may also affect the harm.", "Alcohol abuse may affect not only the incidence of diseases, injuries and other health conditions, but also the course of disorders and their consequences for people.", "There are gender differences in mortality and morbidity due to alcohol, as well as levels and patterns of alcohol use.", "The percentage of deaths due to alcohol among males is 7.6% of all global deaths, compared to 4.0% of all deaths among women.", "In 2010, the average total alcohol consumption per capita among male and female users worldwide was 21.2 liters for males and 8.9 liters of pure alcohol for females.", "A wide range of alcohol consumption patterns, from the dangerous accidental drinking to drinking large quantities every day, create formidable public health and safety problems in almost all countries.", "One of the main characteristics of a risky drinking pattern is accidental drinking of large quantities, equivalent to 60 grams of pure alcohol or more.", "Ways to reduce the burden caused by the harmful use of alcohol", "The health, safety, and socio-economic problems that are attributable to alcohol can be effectively reduced. This requires action that addresses alcohol consumption levels, patterns and contexts, as well as the broader social determinants of health.", "Countries are the first to bear the responsibility for formulating, implementing, monitoring and evaluating public policies aimed at reducing the harmful use of alcohol.", "There is ample scientific knowledge available to policymakers on the effectiveness and cost-effectiveness of the following strategies:", "Regulating the marketing of alcoholic beverages (especially its marketing to young people);", "Impose controls and restrictions on the availability of alcohol;", "Establish appropriate alcohol-driving policies;", "Reducing the demand for alcohol through taxation and pricing mechanisms;", "Awareness-raising and policy support;", "Providing affordable treatments for people with alcohol use disorders;", "Implementation of screening programs and rapid interventions to combat dangerous and harmful use of alcohol.", "WHO response", "The World Health Organization (WHO) reduces the burden of disease caused by the harmful use of alcohol and strives to save lives, prevent injuries and disease, and improve the well-being of individuals, communities and society at large.", "The World Health Organization (WHO) stresses the need to develop, test and evaluate cost-effective interventions in the field of harmful use of alcohol, and to develop, compile and distribute scientific information on alcohol use, dependence and related health and social impacts.", "In 2010, the World Health Assembly adopted a resolution endorsing a global strategy to reduce the harmful use of alcohol.", "The resolution urged countries to strengthen national responses to public health problems arising from this phenomenon.", "The Global Strategy to Reduce the Harmful Use of Alcohol is a collective commitment by WHO Member States to continue work to reduce the global disease burden caused by the harmful use of alcohol.", "The strategy includes evidence-based policies and interventions that, if enforced and implemented, can protect health and save lives.", "The strategy also contains a set of principles that guide policy development and implementation. It also identifies priority areas for action at the global level, recommends targeted areas for action at the national level, and gives a strong mandate to the World Health Organization to strengthen action at all levels.", "Policy options and interventions available for action at the national level can be grouped into ten recommended target areas, each supporting and complementing the other.", "These ten areas are:", "Leadership, awareness and commitment;", "Health services response;", "Community work;", "Alcohol driving policies and countermeasures;", "Availability of alcohol;", "Marketing of alcoholic beverages;", "Pricing policies;", "Methods to reduce the negative effects of alcohol and alcohol poisoning;", "Reducing the public health impact of illicit alcohol produced outside the formal sector;", "Monitoring and surveillance.", "The World Health Organization has developed the Global Information System on Alcohol and Health in Order to actively work on displaying data on levels and patterns of alcohol consumption, health and social impacts that can be attributed to alcohol, and policy responses at all levels.", "Successful implementation of the strategy will require joint action by countries, ensuring effective global governance, and engaging all stakeholders in an appropriate manner.", "With effective cooperation, the negative health and social effects of alcohol use can be reduced.", "1 Based on the 2014 Global Status Report on Alcohol and Health", "2 The global strategy refers only to the public health effects of alcohol consumption, and in no way affects religious beliefs or cultural norms.", "The concept of \u201charmful use of alcohol\u201d in this context differs from its \u201cconcept\u201d as a diagnostic category in the classification of mental and behavioral disorders in the tenth revision of the International Classification of Diseases (WHO, 1992).", "3 The term disability-adjusted life years expands the scope of the concept of years of life lost due to premature death to include the equivalent of those years in which he enjoys \"health\" and lost his life as a result of his ill health or disability."]